    <h5 class="en">The Rainforest</h5>
    <img class="regnskovbillede"src="rainforest.jpg" alt="the rainforest">
    <p>Did you know that in the past the land was covered by 14% rainforest and now it is only covered by 6%?
      <br> 8% of the earth’s rainforests have been cut down for agricultural use and for palm oil plantations. The rainforest is important for everyone, yet no one cares for it. We humans need trees as it protects the climate by converting CO2 into oxygen.

      <br><a href="regnskov.html">Read more</a></p>
  </div>

  <div class="vand">
    <h5 class="to">Water rising</h5>
    <img class="vandbillede" src="water.jpg" alt="Iceberg melting">
    <p>The water level will rise above 1 meter by 2100 meter if we continue to emit CO2 as we do right now.  The 20% of the world's population that is living on small islands, in low-lying countries with long coastlines or close to melting glaciers, will be flooded. Another 10% of the world's population live in areas where there is direct contact with ice and snow, which melts as temperatures continue to rise.
      <br><a href="#">Read more</a></p>
  </div>

